<!-- RecordHandler - a tool to help organize and unify data transactions while outside of an RDF model                  -->
<!-- ======                                                                                                             -->
<!-- This tool is used for the storage of data before it is put into an RDF model. For the initial fetch and post       -->
<!--     translation the information is stored in this type of structure.
<!--                                                                                                                    --> 
<!-- ===== PARAMETERS =====                                                                                             -->
<!-- Directory - the file system location that the records within this record handler will be stored.                   -->
<!--      This can be set to any valid location with the correct read and write permissions.                            -->    
<!-- Format - specifies which type of data storage will be used to store the records in the given directory             -->
<!--     Possible Values:                                                                                               -->
<!--         text - This value causes each record to be stored in individual text files.  Usually used only for initial -->
<!--                    testing and workflow planning due to the performance being much worse with this format.         -->
<!--         binary - The optimized and hidden setting. It will cause there to be a file for all the records.           -->
<!--                    Through the use of a command line call to harvester-recordhandler the contents can be inspected -->
<!--                    for more information please see the -->

<config>
    <directory>harvested-data/record/</directory>
    <format>text</format>
</config>